<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-26T08:05:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-26T08:05:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10849: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic
                                Fleet</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval
                                Operations</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="92" xml:id="d438fn92">Copy
                                transmitted to the Department by the Navy Department.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-26T21:05:00+08:00">October 26, 1937—9:05
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 26—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>0026. Reference orders regarding opening fire on planes in self defense,
                            do not believe such attacks probable but issuance and publicity of this
                            order will undoubtedly result in more care being observed in avoiding
                            such action by planes of opposing forces. Commanding General has been
                            advised gravity of such action and that authority should be used with
                            greatest care.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>